args:
As the party reels from Patia's death, Carmen
appears and claims there is a way to revive
the dead. Soon thereafter, Mikoto also dies!
A moment later, Norwin declares to the group
that he has puzzled out the real culprit.
Everyone spread out and look for Patia!
I sense no breathing; she certainly\nappears to have passed.
Yeah, but she's not DEAD dead—she's\njust all crammed inside one'a these\nlittle creepaziod dolls here.
So we can bring her and everyone\nelse back, right? ...Right?
I fear that may be wishful thinking.
Perhaps, but good luck trying to force\nthat miscreant to reveal it!
Aw, you're gonna get me soaked\nwith all these boo-hoo tears!
You scamps did good to find this place.\nAren't you the smartest widdle duckies?\nYes you are!
You are SO infuriating, Carmen!\nGo stick your snout somewhere else!
Yeah, I thought you were an overseer or\na guide or whatever, but you mostly just\nshow up and tick everybody off.
Ouch, that hurts. Right in the ol' kisser!\nBuuut, fine. You want to know the score?\nHere it is...

This is a prison for souls: A place where
those who lose the game are trapped.
Think of it as a rumpus room where
Scylla keeps her personal collection.
You can't mean she thinks of these foul\ndolls as a COLLECTION?!

I can and do! Scylla just loves to capture
live souls so she can look at 'em and
play with 'em and... Well, whatever
she wants to do, I suppose.
So she turns souls into dolls and stores\n'em right here in this cavernous cave.\n...Betcha didn't see THAT coming! Zing!
Technically, no—but it's only a matter\nof time before Scylla gobbles 'em up.\nGotta get that fresh soul flavor, am I right?
Carmen, is there any way to\nreturn our friends to normal?
Oh sure—and it's a real wowser of a\nmethod. But THAT'S something you\nwon't learn until the end of the game.
I wish you would cease your blabbering\nand just tell us the plain truth for once!

Truth? Lady, I've told you nothing BUT the
truth—that's just how I was made! In fact,
I'll drop one more truthbomb on you right
now about your big final prize.
As you know, the person who survives to\nthe end can choose to live and leave this\nisland. Buuuuut...
They can ALSO serve as a\nsubstitute for the others.

Yep! If they choose to die and let Scylla
devour their soul, all their little pals get
to leave the island without becoming
scrumptious spiritual snackies.
Hark the noble, self-sacrificing heart!\n...Makes great patter, am I right?
So if the last remaining person chooses to\nsacrifice themselves, the rest get to live?
Did I stutter? Seriously, it's not that\ncomplicated. One life in exchange for\na whole bunch of 'em. What a deal!
But then the last person has to die.\nLike, REALLY die.
I'd always thought I'd be ready to\nsacrifice myself for others, but...
It is not courage to run toward one's own\ndeath without thought or pause. Such a\ndecision is difficult for all living creatures.
And even if he did agree to do it,\nwe'd still have to trust him.
And trust is very hard to come by\nin these dark days, it would seem.
What, you think he'll betray everybody and\nleave us to die here while he sails off into\nthe sunset? Do you even KNOW him?!
No, that's not what I mean—I'm referring\nto the fact that Scylla is one of us.
I don't want to doubt him, but we can't\nignore the possibility that she is him.
Of course, it's the same for all of us,\nwhich means we're all under suspicion.
If it's only the person who survives until\nthe end who gets the right to choose,\nthat means the others are already dead.
Even before all that, the notion of\nassuming someone will die for the\nrest of us is nigh-unthinkable.
Agreed—but in that case,\nwhat are our options?
Carmen? How do we win this game?
You're asking that NOW? Sheesh!\nBut yeah, the way to win is to be the\nlast person standing. I mean, dur.
That's not what I mean, exactly.
That's how I can win over everyone else,\nbut I want to know how we can ALL win.
Ooooooo! Now THAT is an interesting\nquestion, my sylvan friend.
For example, if we discover Scylla and\ndefeat her, does that mean we've won?
...Huh. You know what? I have no idea.\nIt's actually never come up before.
Although this IS Scylla's island, so if she\nwas gone, I imagine lots of other things\nwould also end up gone.
Right then. We find Scylla, crush her,\nand end this charade for good!
Uuugh, you people are sooo naive.\nYou're just little pieces on a board,\nbut Scylla is the one moving you around!
You're not even fighting on the same level;\nshe'll wipe the floor with you!
Then does that make YOU\nour opponent, Carmen?
What? No. That's dumb. If you're pieces\non a board, then I'm more like...the board.\nIt's not even an option to fight me.
In that case, further dialogue is useless.\nI will slay everyone and become the victor.
No matter who among us is Scylla,\nthe end result will be the same\nso long as I cut everyone down.
Once this game is at an end, I will simply\noffer up my soul in exchange for yours.
I am already one with nature; it will\nchange little for my soul to be vacated\nfrom this earthly vessel.
My existence will simply continue\nin a different form.
And what if YOU are Scylla?!
I cannot prove a negative. All that can\nbe done is to ask that you trust me.
You talk like this is easy, but I know you\nunderstand the gravity of this situation.
Still, at this point your plan might be\nbetter than going around in circles forever.
I don't know about the others,\nMikoto, but I trust you.
Then perhaps this marks the end\nof our troublesome situation.
Of course. I have no reason not to.
Then leave this duty to me.
That is not the case. However, I... I... URK!
But no one DID anything to him.
The culprit in all of this. I know who has\nkilled Mikoto and all the others.
Then TELL us, for the love of all!
